## Key Insights
Cross-domain discovery depends on partition bridges and similarity thresholds. Bridge topology is the primary lever. The similarity floor (0.5) can be lowered for broader cross-domain reach but risks quality degradation.

## Connections
Decay promotes fresh content; breakthrough floors accumulate validated cross-domain insights. This creates a positive feedback loop for cross-domain discovery quality.

## Foundation
Embedding similarity, LLM voicing, partition boundaries, explicit bridges. Bridge topology matters most for cross-domain optimization.

## Open Questions
Optimal bridge density scaling and whether cross-domain pairs need different similarity thresholds.